# Social Conflict

Not all conflicts end in bloodshed. The negotiation with the guild master, the debate before the council, the interrogation of the captured spy—these confrontations matter as much as sword fights but resolve through words rather than weapons.

Social combat applies Autumn Phoenix RPG's core mechanics to social conflicts. Instead of attacking Guard to deal Vitality damage, you attack Composure to break an opponent's social resistance. The same Momentum economy, stances, and tactical decisions that govern physical combat apply to social confrontations.

